==English==
===Etymology===
{{L.}} fides: faith + commissus (p.p. of committo) : to combine / hold together.
===Noun===
{{en-noun2|'''fideicommissum'''|'''[[fideicommissa]]'''}}

#A [[benefit]] bequeathed to a beneficiary who inherits the benefit, subject to the [[obligation]] of [[bequeath]]ing it to another.
#*I bequeath my farm to my brother John on condition that he bequeaths it to his son Peter. The farm is [[entail]]ed or [[burden]]ed by a '''fideicommissum'''.
